-=Synopsis=-

In 2004, George Jones celebrated 50 years as a country music legend with a tribute concert recorded for PBS&#039;s SOUNDSTAGE program. Hosted by Reba McEntire, the concert presents live performances of Jones&#039;s greatest hits by 20 country luminaries, including Emmylou Harris, Kris Kristofferson, Alan Jackson, Vince Gill, Kenny Chesney, and Martina McBride.

-=Review=-

George Jones continues to produce his own inimitable brand of country music, which has produced hits in every decade of the second half of the 20th Century.

Soundstage have marked his 50th anniversary as a recording artist with a 2007 release George Jones & Friends: A 50th Anniversary Tribute Concert, which was recorded at the Roy Acuff Theatre in Nashville Tennessee.

Twenty of country music&#039;s biggest stars take a turn at interpreting Jones&#039; country classics, and the great man himself performs solo and duets with several of the guests.

The double DVD set features bonus interviews and music videos.
